  "_comment": "Mock supplier dataset (~40 records) for the supplier-discovery demo. ~30 copper-cable suppliers across many countries + ~10 noise suppliers in other categories. Four narrative cases are deliberately seeded so the demo lands: (1) DUPLICATE PAIR — sup_003 'Nordic Cable Co' and sup_004 'Nordic Cable Company Ltd' share domain nordiccable.example; entity resolution in store.py collapses them into one golden record. (2) EXPIRED CERT — sup_002 'Rheinland Kupferkabel GmbH' claims an active ISO 9001 but the mock IAF registry (verify.py) returns it as expired, so it is DEMOTED/flagged rather than dropped. (3) SANCTIONED ENTITY — sup_007 'Adria Copper Trading Ltd' (CY) scores well on paper and is in the EU, but hits the mock OFAC list, so it is DROPPED at the hard-filter gate with a visible reason. (4) UNVERIFIED F500 CLAIM — most fortune500_customers entries are self-reported; verify.py corroborates only a tiny allow-list, so e.g. sup_017's 'Apple' claim is shown but flagged 'unverified'. financial_health / esg_score are 0-1 mock scores; fortune500_customers are self-reported claims until verified.",
